{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 106,
      "text": "Not the-- she did not receive us with open arms, but nevertheless, she did permit us into the house, and that's where we lived for the duration of the next four years.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 107,
      "text": "In the four years, I begin to think that, in fact, I have an uncle and aunt that might be in the United States.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 108,
      "text": "As a confused youngster, at 13 when the war broke out, normal thinking was not part of my life anymore from the age of 13 on to the age of 18.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 109,
      "text": "So I didn't know much about relatives, where they all are, what their names are, what their birthdays are.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 110,
      "text": "I just had no knowledge.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 111,
      "text": "This was just too long of a span of a young man-- in a young man's time to know any of that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 112,
      "text": "But I did recall that my mother had a brother in the United States and therefore his name would have been Baldinger.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 113,
      "text": "And my mother's name is Baldinger, B-A-L-D-I-N-G-E-R.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 114,
      "text": "And so I began to look for this Baldinger.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 115,
      "text": "And sometime in 1947, my uncle from the United States began to search equally records on whether any of the Baldingers were alive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 116,
      "text": "And we made contact.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 117,
      "text": "I made contact with him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 118,
      "text": "And we began to correspond.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 119,
      "text": "And he secured an affidavit in the United States, where he found-- he was not a man of great means.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 120,
      "text": "But he did find an employer who was willing to sign an affidavit that I would be permitted to come to this country, and I would not be a burden on the country if he brought me over.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 121,
      "text": "He would-- this employer would give me work and all that, and even that didn't help.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
